& [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060] is a SOP-HG graph
  + [N:event:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060] is SOP fiber FPGA bridge realization
    = role: direct_focus_turn
  + [N:surface:speed_surface] is frame_rate, frame_period, pipeline_latency, route_latency, and interpreter_latency
  + [N:surface:bandwidth_surface] is fiber_bandwidth, fpga_route_width, io_bandwidth, and memory_bandwidth
  + [N:surface:hardware_routable_surface] is frame sync, channel routing, track routing, payload lanes, checksums, buffers, and backpressure
  + [N:surface:interpreter_surface] is semantic meaning assignment, novel inference, reconstruction, truth, identity, safety, and proof integration
  + [N:metric:effective_throughput] is frame_rate times frame_payload_width bounded by bandwidth surface and backpressure
  + [N:metric:semantic_fidelity] is source, boundary, outside, proof, trace, and reconstruction status
  + [N:outside:bridge_boundary] is implemented HDL, bitstream, board design, measured performance, and semantic correctness proof

  / [E:defines:sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060] -(defines; event=N:event:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060; speed=N:surface:speed_surface; bandwidth=N:surface:bandwidth_surface)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060]
    = realization: speed is frame-rate and latency specific, while bandwidth is physical and routing width
  / [E:partitions:bridge_work_060] -(partitions; hardware=N:surface:hardware_routable_surface; interpreter=N:surface:interpreter_surface; fidelity=N:metric:semantic_fidelity)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060]
    = realization: hardware can move and gate frames massively in parallel, while semantic interpretation remains governed unless compiled
  / [E:measures:throughput_boundary_060] -(measures; throughput=N:metric:effective_throughput; bandwidth=N:surface:bandwidth_surface; outside=N:outside:bridge_boundary)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060]
    = caution: throughput estimates need hardware implementation and measurement before becoming performance claims
  / [E:bounds:bridge_boundary_060] -(bounds; event=N:event:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060; outside=N:outside:bridge_boundary)> [Graph:2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge_060]
    = caution: semantic fidelity is not guaranteed by raw bandwidth

  = inside: SOPFiberFPGABridge.sop, frame clock, bandwidth surface, route width, hardware/interpreter partition, semantic fidelity boundary
  = boundary: hardware-shaped SOP specification for fiber FPGA routing
  = outside: implemented HDL, bitstream, board design, measured timing, measured bandwidth, power, thermal behavior, and semantic correctness proof
